gomodel:SYNGO_2588  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: \"Recombinant Slitrk3 localizes to inhibitory postsynaptic sites\"\n- \"A majority of YFP-Slitrk3 puncta colocalized well with clusters of the inhibitory postsynaptic scaffold gephyrin apposed to VGAT (Fig. 2a) and with GABA receptor γ2 clusters apposed to VGAT (Fig. 2b), but hardly colocalized with excitatory postsynaptic scaffold PSD-95 or VGLUT1 (Fig. 2c,d). The presence of YFP-Slitrk3 puncta in dendrites but not axons of transfected neurons indicated postsynaptic and not presynaptic accumulation (Supplementary Fig. 3).\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Slitrk3 expressed in fibroblasts triggers only inhibitory presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons of cocultured rat hippocampal neurons. Recombinant Slitrk3 preferentially localizes to inhibitory postsynaptic sites.\"\n\n- \"The full-length cDNAs for mouse Slitrk1 (clone ID: mKIAA1910), Slitrk2 (40060548), Slitrk3 (6844461), Slitrk4 (40096585), Slitrk6 (4832410J21) and human PTPδ (40027582) were purchased from Kazusa DNA Research Institute, \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2588" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
